<LEADPARA>  Abraham S. Bolsky, who 30 years ago erected the city's first building to
exceed the height limit of 13 stories and built some of the tallest buildings
in the West, died of heart failure Thursday. He was 68.;    Mr. Bolsky was
president of Tishman Construction Corp. of California and executive vice
president of its parent firm, the New York-based Tishman Realty &amp; Construction
Co.  </LEADPARA>
