<HEADLINE>  A.S. BOLSKY, 68, ERECTED SKYSCRAPERS  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Obituaries  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     During his 37 years at Tishman, he directed construction of more than 50
major developments in the West, including three of Los Angeles' largest
buildings -- the 48-story Wells Fargo Bank Building, the Broadway Plaza
complex and the Twin Towers in Century City, company spokesman Bernie Roswig
said.;    More recently, he supervised construction of the Ronald Reagan
Building in downtown Los Angeles and the Rodeo Collection in Beverly Hills,
Roswig said.;    Mr. Bolsky was born in Connecticut and raised in New York.;  
 In 1960, he built the 21-story 615 South Flower Building, the city's first
structure to exceed 13 stories, Roswig said. Taller buildings followed with
the advent of new engineering and construction techniques that would ensure
safety during earthquakes.;    Mr. Bolsky is survived by his wife, Helen, and
